    {
      "content": "Configure a point-to-site VPN connection to an Azure Virtual Network | Microsoft Azure",
      "pos": [
        26,
        112
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Securely connect to your Azure Virtual Network by creating a point-to-site VPN connection.",
      "pos": [
        130,
        220
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Configure a point-to-site VPN connection to an Azure Virtual Network",
      "pos": [
        535,
        603
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> This article applies to point-to-site connections for virtual networks that are created in the classic deployment mode.",
      "pos": [
        607,
        739
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "At this time, point-to-site connections to a virtual network created in the Azure Resource Manager deployment mode are not supported.",
      "pos": [
        740,
        873
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following procedure will walk you through the steps to create a secure point-to-site connection to a virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        875,
        996
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Although configuring a point-to-site connection requires multiple steps, it's a great way to have a secure connection from your computer to your virtual network without acquiring and configuring a VPN device.",
      "pos": [
        997,
        1205
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There are three main parts to configuring a point-to-site VPN: the virtual network and VPN gateway, the certificates used for authentication, and the VPN client that is used to connect to your virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        1206,
        1415
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The order in which you configure each of these is important, so don't skip steps or jump ahead.",
      "pos": [
        1416,
        1511
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1517,
        1607
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create a virtual network and a VPN gateway<ept id=\"p1\">](#create-a-virtual-network-and-a-vpn-gateway)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1611,
        1665
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Create your certificates<ept id=\"p1\">](#create-your-certificates)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1669,
        1725
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Configure your VPN client<ept id=\"p1\">](#configure-your-vpn-client)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "Create a virtual network and a VPN gateway",
      "pos": [
        1730,
        1772
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A point-to-site connection requires a virtual network with a dynamic routing gateway.",
      "pos": [
        1776,
        1861
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following steps will walk you through creating both.",
      "pos": [
        1862,
        1918
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Create a virtual network",
      "pos": [
        1924,
        1948
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1953,
        1984
      ],
      "content": "Log in to the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Azure portal<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "In the lower left corner of the screen, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>New<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        1988,
        2042
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In the navigation pane, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Network Services<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and then click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Virtual Network<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2043,
        2130
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Custom Create<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to begin the configuration wizard.",
      "pos": [
        2131,
        2189
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        2193,
        2316
      ],
      "content": "On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Virtual Network Details<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, enter the following information, and then click the next arrow on the lower right."
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Name<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: Name your virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        2323,
        2359
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example \"VNetEast\".",
      "pos": [
        2360,
        2383
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This will be the name that you'll refer to when you deploy VMs and PaaS instances to this VNet.",
      "pos": [
        2384,
        2479
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Location<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: The location is directly related to the physical location (region) where you want your resources (VMs) to reside.",
      "pos": [
        2486,
        2613
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, if you want the VMs that you deploy to this virtual network to be physically located in East US, select that location.",
      "pos": [
        2614,
        2745
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can't change the region associated with your virtual network after you create it.",
      "pos": [
        2746,
        2831
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        2835,
        2967
      ],
      "content": "On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>DNS Servers and VPN Connectivity<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, enter the following information, and then click the next arrow on the lower right."
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>DNS Servers<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: Enter the DNS server name and IP address, or select a previously registered DNS server from the shortcut menu.",
      "pos": [
        2974,
        3101
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This setting does not create a DNS server, it allows you to specify the DNS servers that you want to use for name resolution for this virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        3102,
        3252
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you want to use the Azure default name resolution service, leave this section blank.",
      "pos": [
        3253,
        3340
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3347,
        3400
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Configure Point-To-Site VPN<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: Select the checkbox."
    },
    {
      "content": "On the  <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Point-To-Site Connectivity<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, specify the IP address range from which your VPN clients will receive an IP address when connected.",
      "pos": [
        3404,
        3548
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There are a few rules regarding the address ranges that you are able to specify.",
      "pos": [
        3549,
        3629
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It's very important to verify that the range that you specify doesn't overlap with any of the ranges located on your on-premises network.",
      "pos": [
        3630,
        3767
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Enter the following information, and then click the next arrow.",
      "pos": [
        3771,
        3834
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3838,
        3906
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Address Space<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: Include the Starting IP and CIDR (Address Count)."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3910,
        3978
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Add address space<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: Add only if required for your network design."
    },
    {
      "content": "On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Virtual Network Address Spaces<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, specify the address range that you want to use for your virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        3982,
        4102
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "These are the dynamic IP addresses (DIPS) that will be assigned to the VMs and other role instances that you deploy to this virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        4103,
        4243
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It's especially important to select a range that does not overlap with any of the ranges that are used for your on-premises network.",
      "pos": [
        4244,
        4376
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You'll need to coordinate with your network administrator, who may need to carve out a range of IP addresses from your on-premises network address space for you to use for your virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        4377,
        4570
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Enter the following information, and then click the checkmark to begin creating your virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        4574,
        4675
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Address Space<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: Add the internal IP address range that you want to use for this virtual network, including Starting IP and Count.",
      "pos": [
        4679,
        4811
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It's important to select a range that does not overlap with any of the ranges that are used for your on-premises network.",
      "pos": [
        4812,
        4933
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You'll need to coordinate with your network administrator, who may need to carve out a range of IP addresses from your on-premises network address space for you to use for your virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        4934,
        5127
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Add subnet<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: Additional subnets are not required, but you may want to create a separate subnet for VMs that will have static DIPS.",
      "pos": [
        5131,
        5264
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Or you might want to have your VMs in a subnet that's separate from your other role instances.",
      "pos": [
        5265,
        5359
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Add gateway subnet<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>: The gateway subnet is required for a point-to-site VPN.",
      "pos": [
        5363,
        5442
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Click to add the gateway subnet.",
      "pos": [
        5443,
        5475
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The gateway subnet is used only for the virtual network gateway.",
      "pos": [
        5476,
        5540
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When your virtual network has been created, you will see <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Created<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> listed under <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Status<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> on the networks page in the Azure portal.",
      "pos": [
        5544,
        5678
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Once your virtual network has been created, you can create your dynamic routing gateway.",
      "pos": [
        5679,
        5767
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Create a dynamic routing gateway",
      "pos": [
        5773,
        5805
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5810,
        5945
      ],
      "content": "In the Azure portal, on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Networks<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, click the virtual network that you just created, and navigate to the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Dashboard<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> page."
    },
    {
      "content": "Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Create Gateway<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, located at the bottom of the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Dashboard<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> page.",
      "pos": [
        5949,
        6023
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A message will appear asking <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Do you want to create a gateway for virtual network \"yournetwork\"<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        6024,
        6123
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Yes<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to begin creating the gateway.",
      "pos": [
        6124,
        6168
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It can take around 15 minutes for the gateway to create.",
      "pos": [
        6169,
        6225
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Create your certificates",
      "pos": [
        6230,
        6254
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Certificates are used to authenticate VPN clients for point-to-site VPNs.",
      "pos": [
        6256,
        6329
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This procedure has multiple steps.",
      "pos": [
        6330,
        6364
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Use the following links to complete each step, in order.",
      "pos": [
        6365,
        6421
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6426,
        6574
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Generate a self-signed root certificate<ept id=\"p1\">](#generate-a-self-signed-root-certificate)</ept> - Only self-signed root certificates are supported at this time."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6578,
        6693
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Upload the root certificate file to the Azure portal<ept id=\"p1\">](#upload-the-root-certificate-file-to-the-management-portal)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6697,
        6761
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Generate a client certificate<ept id=\"p1\">](#generate-a-client-certificate)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6765,
        6853
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Export and install the client certificate<ept id=\"p1\">](#export-and-install-the-client-certificate)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "Generate a self-signed root certificate",
      "pos": [
        6859,
        6898
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "One way to create an X.509 certificate is by using the Certificate Creation Tool (makecert.exe).",
      "pos": [
        6903,
        6999
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To use makecert, download and install <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft Visual Studio Express 2013 for Windows Desktop<ept id=\"p1\">](https://www.visualstudio.com/products/visual-studio-express-vs.aspx)</ept>, which is free of charge.",
      "pos": [
        7000,
        7191
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Navigate to the Visual Studio Tools folder and start the command prompt as Administrator.",
      "pos": [
        7195,
        7284
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7288,
        7508
      ],
      "content": "The command in the following example will create and install a root certificate in the Personal certificate store on your computer and also create a corresponding <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>.cer<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> file that you'll later upload to the Azure portal."
    },
    {
      "content": "Change to the directory that you want the .cer file to be located in and run the following command, where <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>RootCertificateName<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> is the name that you want to use for the certificate.",
      "pos": [
        7512,
        7693
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you run the following example with no changes, the result will be a root certificate and the corresponding file <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>RootCertificateName.cer<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        7694,
        7835
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7838,
        8069
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> Because you have created a root certificate from which client certificates will be generated, you may want to export this certificate along with its private key and save it to a safe location where it may be recovered."
    },
    {
      "content": "Upload the root certificate file to the Azure portal",
      "pos": [
        8189,
        8241
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you generated a self-signed root certificate in the earlier procedure, you also created a <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>.cer<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> file.",
      "pos": [
        8246,
        8353
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You'll now upload that file to the Azure portal.",
      "pos": [
        8354,
        8402
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Note that the .cer file doesn't contain the private key of the root certificate.",
      "pos": [
        8403,
        8483
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8487,
        8599
      ],
      "content": "In the Azure portal, on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Certificates<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page for your virtual network, click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Upload a root certificate<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8603,
        8706
      ],
      "content": "On the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Upload Certificate<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page, browse for the .cer root certificate, and then click the checkmark."
    },
    {
      "content": "Generate a client certificate",
      "pos": [
        8712,
        8741
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "On the same computer that you used to create the self-signed root certificate, open a Visual Studio command prompt window as administrator.",
      "pos": [
        8746,
        8885
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Change the directory to the location where you want to save the client certificate file.",
      "pos": [
        8889,
        8977
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>RootCertificateName<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> refers to the self-signed root certificate that you generated.",
      "pos": [
        8978,
        9062
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If you run the following example (changing the RootCertificateName to the name of your root certificate), the result will be a client certificate named \"ClientCertificateName\" in your Personal certificate store.",
      "pos": [
        9063,
        9274
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Type the following command:",
      "pos": [
        9278,
        9305
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "makecert.exe -n \"CN=ClientCertificateName\" -pe -sky exchange -m 96 -ss My -in \"RootCertificateName\" -is my -a sha1",
      "pos": [
        9311,
        9425
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "All certificates are stored in your Personal certificate store on your computer.",
      "pos": [
        9430,
        9510
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Check <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>certmgr<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> to verify.",
      "pos": [
        9511,
        9537
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can generate as many client certificates as needed based on this procedure.",
      "pos": [
        9538,
        9617
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "We recommend that you create unique client certificates for each computer that you want to connect to the virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        9618,
        9740
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Export and install the client certificate",
      "pos": [
        9746,
        9787
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A client certificate must be installed on each computer that you want to connect to the virtual network.",
      "pos": [
        9792,
        9896
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This means you will probably create multiple client certificates and then need to export them.",
      "pos": [
        9897,
        9991
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To export the client certificates, use <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>certmgr.msc<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        9992,
        10045
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Right-click the client certificate that you want to export, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>all tasks<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, and then click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>export<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        10046,
        10153
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Export the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>client certificate<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> with the private key.",
      "pos": [
        10157,
        10210
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This will be a <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>.pfx<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> file.",
      "pos": [
        10211,
        10238
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Make sure to record or remember the password (key) that you set for this certificate.",
      "pos": [
        10239,
        10324
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Copy the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>.pfx<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> file to the client computer.",
      "pos": [
        10328,
        10372
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "On the client computer, double-click the <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>.pfx<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> file in order to install it.",
      "pos": [
        10373,
        10449
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Enter the password when requested.",
      "pos": [
        10450,
        10484
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Do not modify the installation location.",
      "pos": [
        10485,
        10525
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Configure your VPN client",
      "pos": [
        10530,
        10555
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To connect to the virtual network, you'll also need to configure your VPN client.",
      "pos": [
        10557,
        10638
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The client requires both a client certificate and the proper VPN client configuration in order to connect.",
      "pos": [
        10639,
        10745
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Create the VPN client configuration package",
      "pos": [
        10751,
        10794
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In the Azure portal, on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Dashboard<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> page for your virtual network, navigate to the quick glance menu in the right corner and click the VPN package that pertains to the client that you want to connect to your virtual network.",
      "pos": [
